article.description: Brandon Boyd scored the winning layup with two seconds to go to lift Idaho State over Sacramento State 72-70 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Brandon Boyd's layup lifts Idaho State over Sacramento State
article.linkText: Brandon Boyd's layup lifts Idaho State over Sacramento State
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. -- Brandon Boyd scored the winning layup with two seconds to go to lift Idaho State over Sacramento State 72-70 on Saturday night. Boyd drove past Chibueze Jacobs and finished from the right side of the lane . Sacramento State's Jordan Tolbert missed a half-court heave at the buzzer. The Bengals (7-7, 3-2 Big Sky Conference) led 70-65 on Boyd's 3-pointer with 41 seconds left. Izayah Mauriohooho-Le'afa answered with a 3 to cut the deficit to two at 21 seconds. Tolbert stole it from Balint Mocsan and Marcus Graves tied it for the Hornets (6-7, 0-4) with nine seconds left. Jared Stutzman had 13 points, Kelvin Jones and Chier Maker added 12 points each, and Boyd scored 10 for Idaho State. Graves scored a season-high 27 points on 10-of-16 shooting for Sacramento State. Mauriohooho-Le'afa added 16 points and Joshua Patton had 11.
